There is a standard algorithm called [std::count_if](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/algorithm/count) that counts all elements that satisfy a predicate. This should be the preferred method to use unless you have good reason not to.

~~~
#include &lt;algorithm&gt;

int main(){
    int x[] = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 };

    auto f = [](int a){
        return a &gt; 3;
    };

    return std::count_if(std::begin(x), std::end(x), f);
}
~~~

